post_text: Good afternoon, I would like to correct some information that is currently out. The most current information that we have from the state department of education tells us that local school boards can not make a decision when it comes to executive order 20-59. That was as of last Thursday. The attorney general had been quoted as saying the county can make a decision however as of that time the AG had not put that in writing. Tonight the board is meeting to go over our back to school plan with education options available. They will not be voting on the executive order. At this time the executive order will have to be followed until we are told different.

shared_text:
Pleasanton Schools USD 344‎Red Cross Blood Drive for StuCo
July 22 at 8:58 PM ·

Safety first – ALWAYS!

We follow the highest standards of safety and infection control to ensure the health of donors, volunteers and staff.

-Checking donor, volunteer and staff temperatures before entering the blood drive.

-Red Cross safety protocols include wearing gloves and masks, using sterile collection sets and an aseptic scrub for every donation, and wiping down donor-touched areas after each collection.

-ALL donors, volunteers and staff MUST wear face masks or coverings. (Provided if needed.)

-Following 6-foot social distancing between donors at entry, donation and canteen areas.

-Grab-N-Go canteen consists of Red Cross provided individually wrapped snacks, water and juice.

post_text:
Good evening parents and families,

I apologize for the late notice. Graduation will be on the football field at 2 PM Saturday. Parents and guests should bring lawn chairs and you will be able to sit on the field. We ask that you space yourselves on the field and social distance. This will be the same format that we had planned inside. In addition we will live stream it and have it playing on the radio for you if you choose to remain in your car or at home. We will send links just before graduation. Thank-you for your patience as we navigate this and try to make the very best graduation that we safely can for our seniors.

post_text:
The Kansas Teachers Community Credit Union has extended their scholarship deadline to June 15th due to low application submissions.

Kansas Teachers Community Credit Union is offering (4) $500 scholarships for the 2020 school year
To apply:
 You must be a member of KTCCU (Open an account with $5)

 Provide proof of enrollment in a university, community
college, or trade school

 Submit a 500 word or less essay on the following:

The credit union difference is “People Helping People”. Tell us how you demonstrate this in your life.
 Email your information to mkolarik@kstcu.org by 6-15-2020
on the subject line write KTCCU Scholarship

 Winners will be announced on 7-17-2020. The scholarship money will be deposited into the winner’s credit union
account

Good afternoon everyone,

I would like to give everyone the details on our May 9th Senior recognition. We will meet at the school parking lot and start at 8 PM. We will utilize an FM transmitter and the football field PA system to read the student accolades. We will announce the radio channel the day of the event.

Seniors have been grouped into groups of 5 and will come to the podium to be recognized while maintaining 6 ft social distance. As soon as they are recognized they will return to their car. We will announce all awards and scholarships that have been received at this point. In addition, we will have a photographer on hand to get pictures of the seniors while the students are on the podium. The district will also purchase a copy for each family.

After the last senior is announced please do not leave as we have one more surprise for everyone. Lastly, It is imperative that all families stay in their car throughout the entire time.

Sports in Kansas
April 1, 2019 at 7:10 AM ·

27 years ago: Tonya Baucom of Pleasanton (population 1,216) led SW Missouri St. (now Missouri State) to their first ever Division I Final Four in 1992. She averaged 12.8 points and a team-best 6.4 rebounds for the 31-3 Lady Bears to earn all conference honors two times. That season picked up victories over Kansas, Iowa, UCLA and Ole Miss to reach the Final Four. She was inducted into the Missouri State Hall of Fame in 2007. #sportsinkansas

Photo: Missouri State Media Relations

post_text:
Seniors and parents: In the midst of all the craziness that we have witnessed this year I would like to share a piece of a rainbow with you. We have been working on a new scholarship for our seniors for almost a year now. I am very pleased to announce that everything is now in place for the Donald R. Ray and Betty M. Ray College Scholarship. From what I know the Ray´s were near lifetime residents of Pleasanton and owned a small accounting business.

This scholarship covers 100 percent of all college costs including room and board! The scholarship is funded by a portion of the Ray´s estate that has been placed in a trust that will sponsor a multitude of future seniors. The fund should perpetually cover multiple seniors utilizing only the income generated from the fund, therefore never touching the original principal amount.

Mr. Nolan has sent the scholarship application to all seniors and it has a quick turnaround. Be sure to get it filled out soon.

Happy Easter!

Linn County Health Department
April 3 at 5:41 PM ·

We would like to thank those of you who have been staying at home and using appropriate social distancing (staying 6 feet from others). These efforts seem to be paying off for now as we have stayed at 6 positive cases of COVID-19 Coronavirus this week. Thanks for staying up to date with the situation and complying with our guidelines.

We want to encourage you to continue to stay at home following Governor Kelly’s order to assist us in attempting to keep this virus in check. To be successful, we must all continue to work together to have a chance for success.

Please follow social distancing efforts, wash your hands regularly and stay home unless you absolutely have to travel.
Again, we thank you for your efforts.

Hello BluJay Nation! I am Coach Hendricks, the new Head Football Coach, and I am excited to be a BluJay! While recent events have put an end to athletics for this school year, next year starts TODAY! March 24 at 11:12 AM ·

Good morning! We will begin meal distribution Thursday at 11 am. Note the highlighted area on the back parking lot. You will pull in and make the loop and be heading north and then stop at the single door just past all the windows that you see on the cafeteria. You will remain in your car and someone will bring the meals to you. Please stay in line and stay in your car.

Also please remember I am sure we will have some bugs to work out and that we will continue to improve as the processes kinks are worked out. Lastly, meals will be served Thursday and Friday of this week and then we will follow the rest of the calendar days that we would have normally been in attendance with the last day being May 12th.

If you are on a bus route your meals will leave the building to be delivered just before 11. Please be watching for the delivery. Town stops the van will stop at the central location that the bus stops at. Please remember to keep your spacing as you wait for the van to arrive.

Please be assured that Kansas State Department of Education (KSDE) leaders are in daily communication with the leaders of the Kansas Department of Health and Environment (KDHE) and school superintendents as guidance regarding COVID-19 is changing rapidly. post_text: The JH Scholars bowl team will be hosting their home meet on Thursday, February 20 at 4 pm. I am looking for some volunteers that would be interested in being a reader or a judge for me. I have 11 schools that will be in attendance and will need 10 readers, judges, and timer/score keepers. post_text: Calling all Junior & Senior parents! The Mid-Season Tournament is this week and the After Prom needs your help in providing baked goods (and work service) for the annual bake sale. This bake sale provides about 1/2 of our funds for the After Prom activities. We would like each student to provide at least 1 baked good for sale on TUE, THU & FRI. These can be dropped at the office, to your class sponsor, or brought straight to the commons area prior to game time. If you are available to work the bake sale, please contact me (Tara Carpenter) so that I can get you scheduled. Thank you all in advance for your participation!!
